# {{.ProjectName}} — Agent Guide

This project was scaffolded by the `justgo` CLI and expects ongoing changes to
go through it rather than hand-written boilerplate.

## Stack
- HTTP router: {{.Router}}
{{if .UseDB}}- Database: {{.DBEngine}} via sqlc{{end}}
{{if .UseObs}}- Observability: github.com/goleggo/observer (slog + OpenTelemetry){{end}}

## Adding functionality

Add a new domain (model + repository + usecase + handler + wiring):

    justgo gen <domain>

Add a single layer only (model, repository, usecase, handler, init, routes):

    justgo gen <layer> <domain>

Append an endpoint action to an existing handler + route:

    justgo gen handler <domain> <action> [--method=GET|POST|PUT|DELETE] [--path=/custom/path]

## Rules for editing generated code

- Never hand-edit between the `// [justgo:imports]` / `// [justgo:wire]` markers
  in cmd/{{.ProjectName}}/main.go — `justgo gen <domain>` rewrites these blocks.
- Never hand-edit around the `// [justgo:routes]` marker in
  internal/<domain>/routes.go — use `justgo gen handler` to add routes instead.
- After changing a repository or usecase interface, run `make mock` to
  regenerate mocks rather than hand-editing internal/<domain>/mocks/.
- To change generated boilerplate project-wide, add overrides under
  templates/<router>/<name>.tmpl or templates/<name>.tmpl instead of editing
  already-generated files.
